Program: The Reith Lectures
Title: The Cross of Humiliation
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00h4n75
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 14 Nov 1979
Professor of Political Science at the University of Michigan, Ali Mazrui considers the injustices that have been inflicted on the African people over time in his second Reith lecture. Delivering his lecture from the series entitled 'The African Condition' he explores the sufferances of the African people. In this lecture entitled 'The Cross of Humiliation', Professor Ali Mazrui argues that Africans and people of African ancestry have suffered more humiliation in modern history than any other race. Show less